Anchorage Capital Group Position in Travelport Worldwide LTD (TVPT) Decreased by $13.41 Million; Spruce House Investment Management Has Boosted Its Installed Bldg Prods (IBP) Position by $15.24 Million; Stock Rose

July 24, 2017 - By test

Anchorage Capital Group Llc decreased its stake in Travelport Worldwide Ltd (TVPT) by 43.65% based on its latest 2016Q4 regulatory filing with the SEC. Anchorage Capital Group Llc sold 958,100 shares as the company’s stock declined 3.82% while stock markets rallied. The hedge fund held 1.24 million shares of the transportation services company at the end of 2016Q4, valued at $17.44 million, down from 2.20 million at the end of the previous reported quarter. Anchorage Capital Group Llc who had been investing in Travelport Worldwide Ltd for a number of months, seems to be less bullish one the $1.79 billion market cap company. The stock increased 0.14% or $0.02 on July 21, reaching $14.39. About shares traded. Travelport Worldwide Ltd (NYSE:TVPT) has risen 5.67% since July 24, 2016 and is uptrending. It has underperformed by 11.03% the S&P500.







Spruce House Investment Management Llc increased its stake in Installed Bldg Prods Inc (IBP) by 21.73% based on its latest 2016Q4 regulatory filing with the SEC. Spruce House Investment Management Llc bought 371,786 shares as the company’s stock rose 17.15% with the market. The institutional investor held 2.08M shares of the basic industries company at the end of 2016Q4, valued at $86.00M, up from 1.71 million at the end of the previous reported quarter. Spruce House Investment Management Llc who had been investing in Installed Bldg Prods Inc for a number of months, seems to be bullish on the $1.60 billion market cap company. The stock decreased 1.54% or $0.8 on July 21, reaching $51.15. About shares traded. Installed Building Products Inc (NYSE:IBP) has risen 54.12% since July 24, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 37.42% the S&P500.
Investors sentiment decreased to 1.02 in 2016 Q4. Its down 0.41, from 1.43 in 2016Q3. It fall, as 18 investors sold IBP shares while 42 reduced holdings. 18 funds opened positions while 43 raised stakes. 20.79 million shares or 2.14% less from 21.25 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Pinebridge Investments LP stated it has 2,522 shares. Louisiana State Employees Retirement Sys has 8,000 shares. Riverhead Limited Liability Corp invested in 0% or 500 shares. Emerald Advisers Pa reported 779,526 shares. State Of Tennessee Treasury Department stated it has 0% of its portfolio in Installed Building Products Inc (NYSE:IBP). Nationwide Fund stated it has 12,493 shares or 0% of all its holdings. Gmt Cap Corporation has 0.13% invested in Installed Building Products Inc (NYSE:IBP). State Common Retirement Fund holds 0% or 22,800 shares in its portfolio. Nuveen Asset Mngmt Ltd Limited Liability Company stated it has 0.01% in Installed Building Products Inc (NYSE:IBP). 15,500 are held by California Public Employees Retirement. Zurcher Kantonalbank (Zurich Cantonalbank) has 431 shares. Sei Investments reported 0% of its portfolio in Installed Building Products Inc (NYSE:IBP). 9,300 are held by New England Mngmt. Quantbot Tech LP holds 0% or 962 shares. Millennium Management Ltd Llc owns 7,087 shares or 0% of their US portfolio.
Since January 25, 2017, it had 0 buys, and 10 selling transactions for $42.34 million activity. Elliott Jay P. also sold $143,580 worth of Installed Building Products Inc (NYSE:IBP) shares. Shares for $296,641 were sold by THOMAS MICHAEL H on Wednesday, March 1. 100,000 Installed Building Products Inc (NYSE:IBP) shares with value of $4.60M were sold by NIXON J MICHAEL. The insider Edwards Jeffrey W. sold $31.50 million. Carter Margot Lebenberg sold $114,296 worth of Installed Building Products Inc (NYSE:IBP) on Thursday, June 1.
Among 9 analysts covering Installed Building Products (NYSE:IBP), 7 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 2 Hold. Therefore 78% are positive. Installed Building Products had 13 analyst reports since July 30, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. RBC Capital Markets maintained Installed Building Products Inc (NYSE:IBP) rating on Thursday, October 29. RBC Capital Markets has “Outperform” rating and $26 target. The stock has “Buy” rating by RBC Capital Markets on Monday, June 19. The stock of Installed Building Products Inc (NYSE:IBP) has “Overweight” rating given on Thursday, September 17 by Wood. KeyBanc Capital Markets downgraded the stock to “Sector Perform” rating in Wednesday, January 27 report. On Thursday, July 30 the stock rating was maintained by RBC Capital Markets with “Outperform”. The firm has “Buy” rating by Deutsche Bank given on Friday, August 12. The company was maintained on Monday, May 8 by RBC Capital Markets. The rating was upgraded by SunTrust on Thursday, March 17 to “Buy”. The firm earned “Buy” rating on Tuesday, November 22 by Seaport Global Securities. UBS maintained it with “Buy” rating and $33 target in Friday, August 14 report.
